<subSubSection id="C32A651BFF8A5F2EFF5CFC5A0903FB95" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8F3690FF8A5F2EFF5CFC5A0903FB95" blockId="6.[151,1130,887,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B944EA82FF8A5F2EFF5CFC5A0935FC35" bold="true" box="[151,282,951,974]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C304D13FF8A5F2EFEE8FC5A0A59FC34" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1863" box="[291,630,951,975]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliquemaculatum">
<emphasis id="B944EA82FF8A5F2EFEE8FC5A0A59FC34" box="[291,630,951,975]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Scaphisoma obliquemaculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was redescribed in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA14B61FF8A5F2EFC92FC5A0BCCFC35" author="LOBL I." box="[857,995,951,974]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" pagination="937 - 1006" refId="ref8383" refString="LOBL I. 1971: Scaphidiidae von Ceylon (Coleoptera). Revue Suisse de Zoologie 78: 937 - 1006." type="journal article" year="1971">LÖBL (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. In absence of distinctive characters, I place 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D13FF8A5F2EFE31FC3A0B44FC15" authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1916" box="[506,875,983,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudoscaphosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrithorax">
<emphasis id="B944EA82FF8A5F2EFE31FC3A0B6EFC14" box="[506,833,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Pseudoscaphosoma atrithorax</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with this widely distributed species. The MNHN houses five additional females identified by Pic as 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D13FF8A5F2EFB98FC1A092CFBD4" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudoscaphosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrithorax">
<emphasis id="B944EA82FF8A5F2EFB98FC1A092CFBD4" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">P. atrithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They come from 
<collectingRegion id="49F4F872FF8A5F2EFE08FBFA0A30FBD5" box="[451,543,1047,1070]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, Fort de Kock (present Bukittinggi), and were collected in 1926 by E. Jacobson. They are mounted on a single pin and bear a subsequently given red ‘TYPE’ label.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
